==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Autotrophic
<hw>Au`to*troph"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Auto-</ets> + <ets>trophic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Plant
Physiol.)</fld> <def>Capable of self-nourishment; requiring only
minerals for growth; using carbonate or carbon dioxide as a source of
carbon and simple inorganic nitrogen as a nitrogen source; -- said of
all plants in which photosynthetic activity takes place, and certain
bacteria. It is opposed to parasitism or saprophytism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>of or pertaining to an autotroph.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Autotropism</ent>⟦br⟧
